A simpel introduction to the novel-project A Deep Devotion to Emotion, that has taken me 3 years to write. Which I am currently still writing. Those who have read the entirety of it, has truly loved it, and so I thought I would share.‚†Ä
‚†Ä
The essence of the novel, is to experiment with the concepts of thought and emotion. If you were to share your mind, with someone else, unwillingly. This is the case with the lead character Christopher, whom we find to be struggling with a being reffered to as Jaime.  Jaime is not a real character, but more a concept of Christophers insecurities and fears being physically represented. He will therefore often appear in times of trouble, the interesting part however is how  Christopher will deal with the fact he is the only person aware of this.‚†Ä
If you are interested in this let me know, and be sure to follow me for more üòä‚ù§Ô∏èüòÅ‚†Ä

February Fever is also an older poem that follows suit with Resperation in the sense that. Both poems orientate around this idea that there might be a limit to love. That loving someone, can become unhealthy. In this case lead to self doubt, pity, and paranoia.‚†Ä

I hope you like this piece as much as I do.‚†Ä
